> Translated from the Italian for 'buttery', burrata is a cheese typical of the Puglia region, consisting of a casing of mozzarella filled with soft stracciatella and clotted cream. Serve on top of this warm, spiced salad for an autumn treat.

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @carrot{3}(peeled and halved lengthways), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In the meantime, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Cut the @ciabatta{1}(cut into 1cm slices) into 1cm slices.

Pop them onto a large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Set aside for now.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and fry until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch} (if you have any).

When the carrots are halfway through cooking, turn them. At the same time, bake the ciabatta toasts on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Set aside to cool.

Stir the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} into the onions. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the lentils, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml}(for the lentils) into the pan. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to simmer. Cook until the lentils have softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once cooked, stir in the @harissa paste{50%g} and @butter{20%g} until melted. Remove from the heat.

When the carrots are ready, drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and toss to coat. Toss them into the lentils.

Share the lentils between your #serving bowls{} and arrange over the @wild rocket{20%g} leaves.

Halve your @burrata{125%g} and place in the centre of salad. Drizzle some @olive oil{drizzle} over the rocket and cheese. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Place the ciabatta toasts on the side for dipping.

Enjoy!